Interface Synset<S extends Sense,E extends SynsetRelation,T extends SynsetRelationType,G extends Gloss,X extends Example>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the Sense type
    E - the SynsetRelation type for relations between synsets
    G - the Gloss (i.e. definition) type
    X - the Example type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<S>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BabelSynset

    public interface Synset<S extends Sense,E extends SynsetRelation,T extends SynsetRelationType,G extends Gloss,X extends Example>
extends Iterable<S>
    A general class for a synonym set (synset).

    navigli
